pulltitle: Added the living Celtic languages that were not already included
pullsbody:
Although Irish and Welsh already had entries, the other four did not.

I have only added the base two-letter language codes, on the assumption that people who are directly involved in those communities will add the the four-letter codes if desired.

pull_commit_message: Added the living Celtic languages that were not already included

pullsbody:
The names (both English and native) of `ga-IE` here are nonsensical. I propose to change `ga-IE` and to make it the same as `ga` because `IE` is the default country for `ga`.

For more information on the Irish language and its name(s), see for example here: http://www.lexiconista.com/pdf/LocalizationWithIrish.pdf

Thank you.
pull_repo_desc: List of all the known languages in their English and Native name with locales
pull_commit_message:
name of the Irish language

The names (both English and native) of `ga-IE` here are nonsensical. I propose to change `ga-IE` and to make it the same as `ga` because `IE` is the default country for `ga`.

For more information on the Irish language and its name(s), see for example here: http://www.lexiconista.com/pdf/LocalizationWithIrish.pdf

Thank you.
